The article is a speech given by the President of the United States about the economy. The President discusses the economic philosophy of the past decade, which focused on reducing taxes, deregulation, and prioritizing corporate interests. He argues that this philosophy led to an illusion of prosperity while the economy weakened and the middle class suffered. The President emphasizes his belief in a different approach, rooted in the values of hard work, individual responsibility, and investment in education, clean energy, and infrastructure. He criticizes Republican leaders for opposing his policies and prioritizing the interests of the wealthy. The President concludes by discussing his vision for the future, which includes a strong economy, a growing middle class, and responsible fiscal policies.